## Project rules (enforced by lint, tests, CI, audit-ai-docs)

See `.ai-factory/RULES.md` for full rule list (R1‚ÄìR20). Quick reference:

- **R1** TypeScript hygiene ‚Äî no `as any`, no `!`, no `enum`.
- **R2** Validation at boundaries ‚Äî Zod at every external input.
- **R3** Architectural boundaries ‚Äî domain ‚Üí application ‚Üí infrastructure (one direction).
- **R4** Tests for new public code ‚Äî every export tested with real assertion.
- **R5** Async correctness ‚Äî no floating promises.
- **R6** Errors ‚Äî Error subclasses only, structured.
- **R7** Time/randomness/IO injected via interfaces.
- **R8** Observability ‚Äî OTel spans on public commands/queries.
- **R9** Imports ‚Äî banned: lodash, moment, axios.
- **R10** Naming ‚Äî by location and convention.
- **R11** CI integrity ‚Äî `ci-success` is required check.

For React/Next projects, also R12‚ÄìR20 (see `.ai-factory/RULES.react-next.md`).

For microservices, also IR1‚ÄìIR6 (see `.ai-factory/rules/integration-rules.md`).

