## Workflow

This project uses **AI Factory (aif)** for spec-driven development.

### Required commands

- **`/aif-explore <task>`** ‚Äî when scope is unclear. Saves research to `.ai-factory/RESEARCH.md`.
- **`/aif-plan <task>`** ‚Äî for any non-trivial change. Creates branch, writes plan to `.ai-factory/plans/`.
- **`/aif-implement`** ‚Äî execute plan step by step with checkpoints.
- **`/aif-verify`** ‚Äî **required before commit.** Runs `best-practices-sidecar`, `review-sidecar`, `docs-auditor` over RULES.md and audit-ai-docs.sh probes.
- **`/aif-fix <error>`** ‚Äî targeted bug fix. Reads the plan, knows exactly what was intended.
- **`/aif-commit`** ‚Äî final commit, groups checkpoint commits, pushes.

### Forbidden

- `git commit --no-verify` ‚Äî bypassing pre-commit/pre-push hooks.
- `git push -f` to `main`.
- Skipping `/aif-verify` before PR.
- Adding rules to AGENTS.md / RULES.md without a measurable check.

## Skills available

The following skills auto-activate on relevant queries:

- **`rules-as-tests`** ‚Äî five-layer framework (architecture / meta-tests / spec by example / mutation / living docs). Auto-triggers on questions about ESLint, Stryker, Pact, dependency-cruiser, AI-driven code drift.

Add additional project skills here as you create them. Don't list a skill until its file is committed (see ai-traps.md, lesson #2).

## Sub-agents (Claude Code)

Loaded by AI Factory in `.claude/agents/`:

- **`best-practices-sidecar`** ‚Äî validates code against RULES.md after each `/aif-implement`. Reports violations.
- **`review-sidecar`** ‚Äî two-AI tautology review. Reads tests as if external reviewer with no memory of how they were written.
- **`docs-auditor`** ‚Äî runs `scripts/audit-ai-docs.sh` (drift detection + code-vs-docs probes). Interprets PASS/FAIL.

## Test commands

```bash
npm run test                    # vitest run (unit + audit tests)
npm run test:watch              # vitest watch mode
npm run test:coverage           # with coverage thresholds
npm run test:integration        # *.integration.ts files (real DB)
npm run test:mutation           # Stryker incremental
npm run test-storybook          # Storybook test runner (UI projects)
npx playwright test             # E2E (UI projects)
```

## Validate everything

```bash
npm run validate                # lint + typecheck + format:check + arch:check + test
./scripts/audit-ai-docs.sh     # drift + code-vs-docs probes (~10 sec)
```

## Stack constraints (enforced)

- TypeScript strict + `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`.
- Node.js version pinned in `.nvmrc` ‚Äî CI depends on it.
- ESLint 10 flat config ‚Äî see `eslint.config.mjs`.
- Mutation kill rate ‚â•70% on PR diff (Stryker incremental).
- Coverage thresholds per-module (see `vitest.config.ts`).
- Architecture rules in `.dependency-cruiser.cjs` ‚Äî fail on violation.

## Files NOT to edit without explicit reason

- `.ai-factory/RULES.md` ‚Äî rules are added/changed via PR with rationale, not silently.
- `.dependency-cruiser.cjs` ‚Äî same.
- `eslint.config.mjs` ‚Äî same.
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` ‚Äî same.
- `scripts/audit-ai-docs.sh` ‚Äî additions need a paired negative test (see references/self-testing-docs.md).

